Amazon has released its financial results for Q4 ending 31 December 2016. For the full year, net sales increased 27% to $136 billion, compared to $107 billion in 2015. “Operating income was $4.2 billion, compared with operating income of $2.2 billion in 2015,” said Amazon. Net income was $2.4 billion, compared with net income of $596 million in 2015. Amazon said “tens of millions” of new paid Prime members joined the company during the year, while its Prime Video service expanded to over 200 countries.